President Biden visited the Allentown area to assess the impact of his policies on businesses and people's attitudes. He discussed how the failure to respond quickly to the COVID crisis affected people's mental health and faith. He highlighted the positive effects of increased vaccinations and the availability of healthcare through Obamacare. The President also emphasized the importance of investing in the middle class, creating jobs, and lowering costs for families. He mentioned the benefits of the Child Tax Credit and infrastructure investments. The President acknowledged that there is more work to be done but expressed optimism about the progress made so far. He addressed concerns about the economy and stated that people will eventually realize the positive changes brought about by his policies. The President also discussed the impact of recent strikes on oil prices and expressed concern about the situation. He defended his decision to authorize the strikes and stated that he had sent a report to Congress regarding the matter.